<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Path-Error on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/path-error/</link><description>Recent content in Path-Error on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/path-error/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Is a Directory Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/is-a-directory/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/is-a-directory/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-is-a-directory-error-fix"&gt;Bash Is a Directory Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when you try to execute or read from a path that is a directory, not a file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Directories are not executable or readable as files. When you accidentally point Bash at a directory instead of a file within it, the system returns this error. It often happens due to missing trailing filenames or incorrect path construction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Forgetting the filename&lt;/strong&gt; — running &lt;code&gt;./bin&lt;/code&gt; instead of &lt;code&gt;./bin/script.sh&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing trailing slash in path construction&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;$dir$filename&lt;/code&gt; without &lt;code&gt;/&lt;/code&gt; between them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Source command on a directory&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;source /etc/init.d&lt;/code&gt; instead of a specific file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executable replaced by a directory&lt;/strong&gt; — a file was removed and a directory created in its place.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-append-the-filename-to-the-directory-path"&gt;Fix 1: Append the filename to the directory path&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source /etc/init.d
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Right&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source /etc/init.d/service.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-ensure-path-separator-between-directory-and-file"&gt;Fix 2: Ensure path separator between directory and file&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DIR&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/home/user/configs&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;FILE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;settings.conf&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — missing slash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$DIR$FILE&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Right&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$DIR&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;$FILE&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-verify-the-path-is-a-file-before-using"&gt;Fix 3: Verify the path is a file before using&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; -d &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$PATH&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error: &lt;/span&gt;$PATH&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; is a directory, not a file&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;elif&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; -f &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$PATH&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; source &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$PATH&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-check-whats-at-the-path"&gt;Fix 4: Check what&amp;rsquo;s at the path&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file /path/to/target
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reveals if it&amp;#39;s a directory or file&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ bash /etc/init.d
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: /etc/init.d: Is a directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ cat /tmp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat: /tmp: Is a directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ ./scripts
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: ./scripts: Is a directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="not-a-directory"&gt;Not a Directory&lt;/a&gt; — opposite error, file used where directory expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-such-file"&gt;No Such File or Directory&lt;/a&gt; — path doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist at all.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Bash Not a Directory Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/not-a-directory/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/not-a-directory/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-not-a-directory-error-fix"&gt;Bash Not a Directory Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when you try to &lt;code&gt;cd&lt;/code&gt; into or reference a file path as if it were a directory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a command expects a directory — such as &lt;code&gt;cd&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ls -R&lt;/code&gt;, or path concatenation — but encounters a regular file instead, the system returns &amp;ldquo;Not a directory.&amp;rdquo; This usually means a path component was misidentified.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;cd&lt;/code&gt; into a file&lt;/strong&gt; — accidentally typing &lt;code&gt;cd /etc/hostname&lt;/code&gt; instead of &lt;code&gt;cd /etc&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Path concatenation assumes a directory&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;$dir/file&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;$dir&lt;/code&gt; is actually a file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Symlink points to a file&lt;/strong&gt; — a symlink expected to be a directory actually points to a file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deleted directory replaced by a file&lt;/strong&gt; — a directory was removed and a file created at the same name.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-if-the-path-is-a-directory-before-using-it"&gt;Fix 1: Check if the path is a directory before using it&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; -d &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; cd &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error: &lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; is not a directory&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-verify-the-parent-path-before-file-operations"&gt;Fix 2: Verify the parent path before file operations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;TARGET&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/path/to/location&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; -d &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; is a directory&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;elif&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; -f &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$TARGET&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; is a file&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-dirname-to-extract-the-directory-component"&gt;Fix 3: Use &lt;code&gt;dirname&lt;/code&gt; to extract the directory component&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;FULLPATH&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/etc/hostname&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DIR&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;dirname &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$FULLPATH&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$DIR&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# /etc — works correctly&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-check-symlinks"&gt;Fix 4: Check symlinks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -la /path/to/link
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify what the symlink actually points to&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;readlink -f /path/to/link
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ cd /etc/hostname
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: cd: /etc/hostname: Not a directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ ls /etc/hostname/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls: cannot access &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;/etc/hostname/&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;: Not a directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ source /etc/hosts/config
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: source: /etc/hosts: Not a directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="is-a-directory"&gt;Is a Directory&lt;/a&gt; — opposite error, directory used where file expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-such-file"&gt;No Such File or Directory&lt;/a&gt; — path doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist at all.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>